<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Wilson Wins Gymnastics Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- Blaine Wilson became the fourth  
gymnast to win three American Cup titles, posting the best scores 
in three of six events Saturday to beat American teammate Jason 
Gatson. 
</P>
<P>
	Jennie Thompson completed an American sweep when she edged  
Russia's Elena Produnova for the women's crown. 
</P>
<P>
	Wilson joined former national champions Bart Conner, Mary Lou  
Retton and Kurt Thomas as a three-time winner of the event. 
</P>
<P>
	``To be a part of history is sweet,'' said Wilson, a three-time  
U.S. all-around champion. ``This was definitely my toughest 
American Cup.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Wilson won the title with 57.025 points, earning his best score  
of 9.775 on the rings. He also topped the individual scores with a 
9.575 in the parallel bars and 9.550 in the vault. 
</P>
<P>
	Gatson was second with 56.800 points, unable to top the list on  
any apparatus but posting the second-best score four times. 
</P>
<P>
	``It shows that the U.S. is coming on strong,'' Gatson said.  
``It is a good steppingstone for national championships and world 
championships.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Bulgaria's Jordan Jovtchev was third after posting the best  
scores on the pommel horse and in floor exercise. 
</P>
<P>
	Thompson also didn't post the best score in any single event and  
finished second only once, in the uneven bars. But she managed to 
avoid the trouble that felled former U.S. champion Vanessa Atler 
and defending American Cup titleist Viktoria Karpenko of Ukraine. 
</P>
<P>
	``I was really excited,'' said Thompson, who finished with  
37.861 points. ``My routines were almost as good as I can do 
them.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Produnova led by .419 heading to the final event, the floor  
exercise, but stumbled with a score of 9.012 -- third lowest among 
the eight finalists. Thompson scored a 9.450, finishing with 37.861 
points to Produnova's 37.842. 
</P>
<P>
	Atler, who won three individual-event titles on Friday night,  
finished third after a fall on the uneven bars gave her only a 
score of 8.462. Karpenko was fourth after also struggling on the 
bars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
