<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Blackmun To Lie in Repose at Court </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The body of retired Justice Harry A. Blackmun  
will lie in repose at the Supreme Court building on Monday, and a 
memorial service is scheduled Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Blackmun, who served on the nation's highest court for 24 years  
before his 1994 retirement, died Thursday. He was 90. 
</P>
<P>
	Court spokeswoman Kathy Arberg said Blackmun's coffin will be in  
the court building's Great Hall from 1 p.m. to 8 p.m. Monday, and 
public admittance will begin at 2 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
	Only four other Supreme Court members have had that honor --  
Chief Justices Earl Warren and Warren Burger and Justices Thurgood 
Marshall and William Brennan. 
</P>
<P>
	Blackmun's memorial service will be held at 1:30 p.m. at  
Metropolitan Memorial United Methodist Church. The service will be 
open to the public. 
</P>
<P>
	Burial services will be private.  
</P>
</TEXT>
