<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Unite's Big Red Wins at Gulfstream </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HALLANDALE, Fla. (AP) -- Unite's Big Red swept past heavily  
favored African Dancer in the final 70 yards to win the $250,000 
Pan American Handicap in stakes-record time Saturday at Gulfstream 
Park. 
</P>
<P>
	Panama City rallied to finish third in a field of seven  
5-year-olds and up going 1 1/2 miles over turf. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Mike Smith, Unite's Big Red was timed in 2:23,  
eclipsing the record of 2:23 2-5 established by Eclipse grass 
champion Buck's Boy in last year's Pan American. Buck's Boy carried 
115 pounds; Unite's Big Red broke the record carrying 114 Saturday, 
two less than the favorite. 
</P>
<P>
	The 5-year-old Florida-bred son of Unite paid $13.20, $4 and  
$2.80. African Dancer, at odds-on, paid $2.60 and $2.20. Panama 
City paid $2.60 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the ninth victory in 28 starts for the winner and  
increased his earnings to $603,055. He won three grass stakes last 
year. 
</P>
<P>
	African Dancer was within three-quarters of a length of Deep  
Dive on the far turn the final time around and drew even with the 
pacesetter as they set down for the stretch drive. 
</P>
<P>
	African Dancer put away Deep Dive inside the eighth pole but  
Unite's Big Red, closing fast on the outside, caught him inside the 
sixteenth pole and won going away by 1 1/4 lengths. African Dancer was 
second by three quarters of a length over Panama City who was a 
length in front of a fast closing Rebridled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
