<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Philadelphia Building Blast Hurts 4 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- An explosion blew out the top floor of a  
small apartment building on Saturday, injuring at least four 
people. 
</P>
<P>
	A gas leak in an oven on the second-floor caused the blast, Fire  
Department supervisor Harry Johnson said. A refrigerator motor 
sparked the explosion. 
</P>
<P>
	The explosion blew out the back and side walls of the top floor  
of the three-story building and destroyed the roof. The blast 
started a fire that gutted the structure before firefighters could 
extinguish the flames. 
</P>
<P>
	Tom Bush, 51, who had been working in the basement of a house  
across the street, and Ed Jackson, 62, ran outside in time to see 
two men crawling out of the rubble to the edge of the wrecked third 
floor. They got a ladder and helped the men down. 
</P>
<P>
	``Their shirts were burned off,'' said Bush.  
</P>
<P>
	He ran into the other floors to rouse tenants, including an  
older man who slept through the whole thing. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities said two men had severe burns, and two others  
suffered lesser burns. In addition, an elderly woman complained of 
chest pains. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
