<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Three Illinois Children Found Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NAPERVILLE, Ill. (AP) -- Police are investigating the apparent  
poisoning deaths of three children whose mother has been 
hospitalized for what officers believe was a suicide attempt. 
</P>
<P>
	The mother, Marilyn Lemak, 41, called 911 Friday. When police  
arrived, they discovered the bodies of 7-year-old Nicholas, 
6-year-old Emily and 3-year-old Thomas, said DuPage County State's 
Attorney Joseph Birkett. 
</P>
<P>
	``There is no evidence to suggest that there is any suspect  
outside of the immediate family,'' Birkett said. ``There are 
definite leads being followed up.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Police say the children were caught up in a domestic dispute  
between the parents. Mrs. Lemak and her husband, David, were 
separated and were getting a divorce, Birkett said. 
</P>
<P>
	David Lemak, an emergency room physician, has been cooperating  
with the investigation, Birkett said. 
</P>
<P>
	Marilyn Lemak was hospitalized in fair condition late Friday.  
</P>
<P>
	The children were apparently poisoned, but toxicology results  
from the medical examiner's office are still pending, Birkett said. 
</P>
<P>
	Naperville is 28 miles west of Chicago.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
