<HEADLINE> Sportscaster Kennelly Dies at 65 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	RIDGEWOOD, N.J. (AP) -- Sportscaster John Kennelly, a longtime  
host of the Giants' pregame show on New York's WNEW-AM radio, has 
died. He was 65. 
</P>
<P>
	Kennelly died Friday at his home in Ridgewood after a long  
illness. 
</P>
<P>
	He was a sportscaster in Baltimore before joining WCBS-AM in New  
York as a newscaster in the early 1970s. 
</P>
<P>
	Kennelly became WNEW's sports director a few years later,  
hosting the station's Giants pregame show from the mid-1970s 
through 1991. He became a sports anchor with WBBR-AM and Bloomberg 
Television after leaving WNEW. 
</P>
<P>
	He is survived by his widow, Suzanne, three sons, and four  
brothers. 
</P>
