<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Flyers Acquire Burt from Hurricanes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- The Philadelphia Flyers acquired defenseman  
Adam Burt from the Carolina Hurricanes in exchange for left wing 
Andrei Kovalenko, team officials said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Burt, 30, has spent his entire 11-year NHL career with Carolina.  
He has recorded three assists and 46 penalty minutes in 51 games 
for the Hurricanes this season. He has scored 36 goals and 106 
assists in 626 career games. 
</P>
<P>
	Kovalenko, 28, has one assist and two penalty minutes in 13  
games for the Flyers this year since being acquired from Edmonton 
in exchange for Alexandre Daigle on Jan. 29. He has 136 goals and 
155 assists in 450 games during his seven-year career. He also has 
played for Quebec-Colorado and Montreal. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're not using Kovalenko and we're going to need defensive  
depth through the playoff run,'' Philadelphia president and general 
manager Bob Clarke said in a prepared statement. ``We think that 
Burt is a pretty good player and is going to be a regular on our 
defense.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Philadelphia is winless in its last six games (0-5-1) and 2-9-3  
in their last 14 games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
