<HEADLINE> $40 Tip May Have Come From Heist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WINSTON-SALEM, N.C. (AP) -- A big tip is usually welcome, but  
this one for a short, quick trip to a bank was big enough to make 
cab driver Travis Vaughn a little suspicious. 
</P>
<P>
	Then police told Vaughn his passenger was suspected of robbing  
the bank. 
</P>
<P>
	Vaughn picked the man up at a house Friday morning, drove him to  
a bank branch, then took him back. 
</P>
<P>
	He said his passenger was in and out of the bank in what seemed  
like a minute. 
</P>
<P>
	``He was so calm,'' Vaughn said. ``He didn't rush me. He didn't  
tell me to step on it or anything like that.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Vaughn said he wasn't suspicious until the guy handed him a $50  
bill for the $8.60 fare and told him to keep the change. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said the passenger was Wayne R. Thomas, 40, who they  
identified from surveillance videos made while the bank was being 
robbed. 
</P>
<P>
	Thomas was arrested Friday night on a charge of armed robbery  
and was in jail Saturday in lieu of $100,000 bail, said police Lt. 
Jim Tesh. 
</P>
</TEXT>
